item.title: About
item.dc:creator: a2z-pro
item.content:encoded:
Who are we ?

Travelling Consultancy Pvt. Ltd. is Nepal based travelling consultancy, registered under private company act of Govt. of Nepal, with quality credentials and trustworthy service guides to reach best possible academic heights based on academic merit and financial capacity. Our primary aim is in assisting competent youngsters to achieve academic heights by anchoring them in exemplary overseas travelling institutions at the right time. We excel in our aim through the convictions and hard work of our staff at the network of our agency. We rightly set the academic goals for aspiring Nepalese prospective students facilitating best travelling opportunities in the prestigious colleges and universities across the world. Committed to the objective of integrity and excellence, International is an acknowledged agency across Nepal.

Our International relationship?

It is the nature of our business that mandates us to build relation with foreign colleges and Universities to successfully enroll students in a variety of courses and levels. We have a dedicated team which looks after the departments and commits to ensure effective communication and coordination at both ends. As an travelling consultancy, we cannot overlook the merits of international relations as it is one of the attributes that keeps the wheel moving. We have been successful in winning the trust and appreciation of a lot of travelling institutions abroad and will continue to make our presence yet more felt and more visible. In order to fully exploit the new opportunities now available to us worldwide, we have been pursuing a strategy of internationalization based on our firm foundations of promotion students mobility from Nepal to a host of countries abroad. We are keen on inking more associations so that we can provide Nepali students with the best of course options and institutions. We have been able to meet the targets set on us by foreign travelling partners and look forward to take the associations to newer heights. We would like to assure all our prospective business associates that we are one of the most prominent names when it comes to abroad studies in Nepal, especially in terms of New Zealand, Australia, USA, Japan and Korea, and we can provide them guaranteed results.

Objective and Mission:

International with a team of enthusiastic & dedicated professionals with excellent services is determined to meet the requirements of prospective students seeking to study abroad. We are using all the resources available in and outside the country to achieve the goal of providing the better opportunity for Nepalese students. At International, we understand that each student has different academic and social background as well as his/her truly unique goals for studying overseas. Our objective is to assist them to select the most suitable course and institution based on their personal interests and academic achievement with consummate advice so that they can confidently continue to pursue their travelling goals with achievable success. We value highest possible business ethics and commit to professional standards and integrity, so student can have confidence on our experienced staff that is equipped with updated information available to assist them for identifying students travelling paths for further study. Quality service and high standards of business ethics are the foundation of our organization. We are committed to facilitate the students with relevant information about life, travelling, accommodation, post study opportunities, etc accurately. After knowing students concerned area of study, we endow them with every minute detail regarding the institution they wish to attend. We support students in every aspect and help them to prepare for the future. We provide minute details on each and every facet of student life abroad. So, we affably request the students interested in abroad study to visit our premises once to feel the difference that how we help you to engrave your future and career. Our mission is to make our organization a forerunner in the field of study abroad across Nepal. We believe achieving various milestones in our endeavor and maintain a lead in the market. We are consistent and aggressive to ensure our quality work among Nepalese prospective students.

Doctors also make a difference by helping patients minimize pain, recover from a disease faster or learn to live with..The meaning of health has evolved over time. In keeping with the biomedical perspective, early definitions of health focused on the theme of the body's ability to function; health was seen as a state of normal function that could be disrupted from time to time by disease. An example of such a definition of health is: "a state characterized by anatomic, physiologic, and psychological integrity; ability to perform personally valued family, work, and community roles; ability to deal with physical, biological, psychological, and social stress".

item.title: Welcome to senior care our goal is to make your life better
item.dc:creator: a2z-pro
item.content:encoded: A hospital is a health care institution providing patient treatment with specialized medical and nursing staff and medical equipment. The best-known type of hospital is the general hospital, which typically has an emergency department to treat urgent health problems ranging from fire and accident victims to a sudden illness. A district hospital typically is the major health care facility in its region, with many beds for intensive care and additional beds for patients who need long-term care. Specialized hospitals include trauma centers, rehabilitation hospitals, children's hospitals, seniors' hospitals, and hospitals for dealing with specific medical needs such as psychiatric treatment (see psychiatric hospital) and certain disease categories. Specialized hospitals can help reduce health care costs compared to general hospitals. Hospitals are classified as general, specialty, or government depending on the sources of income received.

item.title: This Is Your Brain on Remote Work
item.dc:creator: a2z-pro
item.content:encoded: Activities to prevent or cure health problems and promote good health in humans are undertaken by health care providers. Applications with regard to animal health are covered by the veterinary sciences. The term "healthy" is also widely used in the context of many types of non-living organizations and their impacts for the benefit of humans, such as in the sense of healthy communities, healthy cities or healthy environments. In addition to health care interventions and a person's surroundings, a number of other factors are known to influence the health status of individuals, including their background, lifestyle, and economic, social conditions and spirituality; these are referred to as "determinants of health." Studies have shown that high levels of stress can affect human health.

item.title: Sigmund Freud
item.dc:creator: a2z-pro
item.content:encoded: Sigmund Freud was an Austrian neurologist and the founder of psychoanalysis, a clinical method for treating psychopathology through dialogue between a patient and a psychoanalyst. Freud was born to Galician Jewish parents in the Moravian town of Freiberg, in the Austrian Empire.

item.title: Alfred Blalock
item.dc:creator: a2z-pro
item.content:encoded: Alfred Blalock was an American surgeon most noted for his work on the medical condition of shock as well as Tetralogy of Fallot commonly known as Blue baby syndrome.

item.title: Edward Jenner
item.dc:creator: a2z-pro
item.content:encoded: Edward Jenner, FRS FRCPE FLS was an English physician who was a contributor to the development of the smallpox vaccine. The practice of vaccination was popularized by Jenner, and since then has been used ubiquitously to prevent several diseases.

item.title: Virginia Apgar
item.dc:creator: a2z-pro
item.content:encoded: Virginia Apgar was an American obstetrical anesthesiologist, best known as the inventor of the Apgar Score, a way to quickly assess the health of a newborn child immediately after birth in order to combat infant mortality

item.title: Hans Asperger
item.dc:creator: a2z-pro
item.content:encoded:
Johann Hans Friedrich Karl Asperger was an Austrian pediatrician, eugenicist, medical theorist, and medical professor. He is best known for his early studies on mental disorders, specifically in children.
Categories

item.title: Terry Dubrow
item.dc:creator: a2z-pro
item.content:encoded: Terry J. Dubrow, M.D., F.A.C.S. is an American plastic surgeon and television personality. He is known for his work on The Swan and for co-hosting Botched with Dr. Paul Nassif. He also appears on The Real Housewives of Orange County with his wife, Heather.

item.title: Edward Jenner
item.dc:creator: a2z-pro
item.content:encoded: Edward Jenner, FRS FRCPE FLS was an English physician who was a contributor to the development of the smallpox vaccine. The practice of vaccination was popularized by Jenner, and since then has been used ubiquitously to prevent several diseases.
